<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-15T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-15T04:00:00-05:00" n="688" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">846G.79693/4–1548: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-15T17:00:00+08:00">April 15, 1948—5
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 17—4:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>678. Embassy learns Minister Commerce [<hi rend="italic">Communications</hi>]
                        expecting reply to his plea regarding Hong Kong–Shanghai air traffic
                        reported Embtel 608 of April 5. Please confirm Embassy’s assumption
                        Department instruction contained Deptel 439 of March 24 remains in
                        force.</p>
                    <p>Repeated Shanghai 278.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>